# Dependency Injection Context

- This repository uses NestJS dependency injection in all Nest-based applications.
- Register dependencies/wiring in Nest `@Module()` composition roots (modules/providers).
- Prefer constructor injection.
- Use `symbol` tokens for all Nest DI contracts (services, use cases, repositories, adapters, gateways).
- Do not inject by concrete class token and do not use string tokens.
- Every injectable dependency must expose an exported `..._SYMBOL` constant and be wired with `provide: ..._SYMBOL`.
- Constructor injection must reference symbol tokens via `@Inject(..._SYMBOL)`.
- Avoid resolving dependencies directly inside domain entities; keep domain types pure.
- Keep DI wiring in application and adapter layers (use cases, services, adapters), not in DTO/schema-only modules.

## Example

```ts
export const GET_USER_USECASE_SYMBOL = Symbol('GET_USER_USECASE_SYMBOL');

@Module({
  providers: [
    { provide: GET_USER_USECASE_SYMBOL, useClass: GetUserUseCase },
  ],
})
export class UserModule {}

export class UserController {
  constructor(
    @Inject(GET_USER_USECASE_SYMBOL)
    private readonly getUserUseCase: IGetUserUseCase,
  ) {}
}
```
